_:N2d3bad36a43d4453be41ad922d265347 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Henrik L Pedersen was appointed Chief Executive Officer and Executive Director of the Board of Associated British Ports (<abbr title=\"Associated British Ports\">ABP</abbr>) in August 2018. <abbr title=\"Associated British Ports\">ABP</abbr> is the UK’s leading port owner and operator. <abbr title=\"Associated British Ports\">ABP</abbr> operates some of the nation’s biggest and most strategically located ports, in the Humber, Southampton and South Wales. Henrik joined <abbr title=\"Associated British Ports\">ABP</abbr> from APM Terminals, a global ports company owned by the Maersk Group, where he served as Chief Commercial Officer. During his 20-year tenure with the Maersk Group he held a wide range of senior leadership roles based in Denmark, USA, China, Panama, Singapore and the Netherlands.</p>\n\n" .
